	Indianapolis: Wimbledon runner-up Andy Roddick withdrew from next weeks Indianapolis Championships, citing a right hip flexor injury on Friday. Thats the same injury that prompted Roddick to pull out of the US Davis Cup teams quarter final at Croatia last week.        
	New Delhi: Anil Khanna, the AITA secretary general, continues as Asias face in the ITF board of directors after being re-elected for a fourth successive term. The AGM of the ITF Friday elected a new board of directors for the 2009-2011 period.      
	Amemded rule  
	Madrid: The Davis Cup final will have to be held in major cities following amendments to the competitions rules on Friday. The ITF made the change at its annual general meeting after Argentina last November used Islas Malvinas Stadium in Mar del Plata, which failed to meet capacity requirements.      
	Hamburg: Former Wimbledon champion Michael Stich will break his 12-year retirement to play doubles at Hamburg meet.      
	Indian youth grab bronze  
	New Delhi: The Indian mixed doubles pair of Pranav Chopra and Prajakta Sawant settled for bronze after losing their semi-final match 12-21, 15-21 against Lu Kai and Bao Yixin of China at the Asia Youth (U-19) badminton tournament in Kuala Lumpur Saturday.      
	Islamabad: The Pakistan Hockey Federation (PHF) has slapped life bans on former hockey captains Mansoor Ahmed and Naveed Alam for misusing the name of the federation and misappropriation of funds, an official of PHF said Saturday.       
