	Rowing  
	Calcutta: Bimal Mishra of JP Hindi Vidyapeeth and Anushka Halder from South Point will participate in the sculls event of the inaugural Asian School Rowing Association (Asra) Regatta to be held at the Bolgoda Lake Rowing Club, Moratuwa in Sri Lanka from Friday.   
	Five schools from Tamil Nadu besides 300 other Asian schools will also participate in the three-day long meet. Namal Rajapaka, the son of Sri Lanka President Mahinda Rajapaksa, is the chairman of the organisation.     
